children.subject: Thanks, having priority would be niceee...my main issue with CS70 is that I tested out of both Math 1A and 1B (miracles do occur) and haven’t taken Math 53 yet.  I never did any AIME work in HS.  The EE16A class has been pretty challenging, but hanging in there.  So I’m not sure how much “sophomore mathematical maturity” I have. I wished I could have fit the CS 70 DeCal offered this semester.  I’m doing well in my CS61A class so far, right on the borderline between an A and a A-, so I wouldn’t necessarily need to be a world-beater in CS 70, just would need a B and up in order to declare. (articulated out of 61B, but could take it just in case I screw up).

Different anon here, if you do decide to take CS 70, it's not really necessary to Phase 1 it. Even if you're put on the waitlist, CS 70 typically expands to accommodate enrollment, in addition to the people who will drop.
I would recommend you take cs70, which help you declare the major early and get priority getting enrolled in classes. I took 70 in my first semester and that is a great decision if I look back then.

history.content:
I am an undeclared L&S freshman but with sophomore standing.  I have 2 classes already earmarked for Phase 1, EE16B since I wanna get a good lab time, and a breadth that possibly will be popular.  I probably will take 2 of the 3 classes listed, so which additional one should I Phase 1?  And which ones would likely still be available later.  I have a pretty good Phase 1 time from what I heard.

I’d like to take the CS C100 class since DeNero is the lecturer, but it’s a terrible time (TTh 6:30).  Plus CS61C is TTh 5:00 which means that Finals are at the same time for both, so I’m not sure if I can take both.  CS70 I’m debating whether I’m ready for it or not, but I’d love to be able to declare sooner than later.  Hard decisions.
history.subject: Which to Phase 1 - CS 70, CS 61C or CS C100?
